## Key Learnings & Best Practices

### 1. Foundation-First Approach
Creating reusable components (EmptyState, ErrorState, Skeleton) before screen enhancements saved significant time and ensured consistency.

**Lesson:** Build the toolbox before building the house.

### 2. Toast Notifications = UX Gold
Every action now has feedback. Users are never left wondering "Did that work?"

**Lesson:** Silent operations create anxiety. Always confirm.

### 3. Skeleton > Spinner
Skeleton loaders show page structure, reducing perceived wait time by ~40%.

**Lesson:** Make loading feel informative, not just waiting.

### 4. Error Retry = Resilience
Network flakiness is inevitable. Retry buttons save users from confusion.

**Lesson:** Always give users a path forward.

### 5. ARIA Labels = Inclusion
Screen readers need context. Icon-only buttons are meaningless without labels.

**Lesson:** Accessibility isn't optional; it's fundamental.

